<br>
I agree with most of what you are saying -except- it is also the community who gives consequences not just an outside entity.  <br>
<br>
Let's take the driving example.  If  you know some one who recklessly speeds all the time but does not get into accidents yet gives the other drivers around him and his passengers strife because of his driving, would you willingly choose that person over another who is also driving to the same destination?  How about if it is a person who drinks a shot or two before driving, never gotten into an accident and never gotten pulled over for it, but is that a person you would -choose- to ride with?  So, we as a commuity take the laws of the road one step further, we don't just say &quot;okay whatever&quot; we do, to some extent, ostracise a person who breaks speeding laws, especially blatantly.<br>
<br>
So... yes, it is Sony's responsibility to do something about those &quot;services&quot; which buy and sell in-game characters, items, and money for RL money and those who deal with them as well.    But, if you are not condemning it, you -are- condoning it and accepting it and making it possible to do it without any repercussions (there has been said many times on many places those that petition or report the known buyers and sellers are jsut tattle-tales and should be ostracised for that).<br>
<br>
I think the choice of breaking the rules in -any- game is wrong.  Does it mean the person is entirely shit?  no.  The person could be a decent person, but he is still wrong for buying or selling.  The -action- is wrong. <p><center><table width="55%"><tr><td align="center">
