In game there is damn little you can do.<br>
Out of game there is not much more.<br>
<br>
To condone it, is to sacrifice your own moral standards.<br>
To condemn it (outside of your own emotional responses), without an effective means to correct it, is futile and only leads to unenjoyment of the game and high blood pressure.<br>
<br>
By all means, take up the banner of your rightousness. Just be certain you are waving it in the faces of those that can fix this. Otherwise you are a petulant preaching griefer who would have nothing to say if there were no soapbox to stand upon.<br>
<br>
I invite you to buy a table at the next Fan Faire.<br>
Set up a petition, make it on legal form.<br>
Get your signatures, make them known to Sony through the avenues that they understand, and will respond to. Waste not your time and efforts here where the combined intellectual level seems lower than my kneecap.<br>
<br>
There is nothing wrong with your take on this travesty. It just seems you are shouting the injustice of not being able to run a mile, to a room full of the blind and paralyzed.<br>
<br>
Now go to your nearest window<br>
open it<br>
stick your head out (toss out some papers while you are at it) <br>
