<br>
The depth and complexity of the arguments presented makes it obvious that &quot;shallow&quot; is the wrong adjective to use in describing people concerned about the integrity of the game sue to rampant rule-breaking.  If anything, the more cavalier ideal of ignoring wrongdoing until it affects <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>you directly</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> seems more shallow to me.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Politics would prolly be a good choice for someone w/ this mentality<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I've already run in one election, thanks.  Maybe I'll go back to it later.  But that wouldn't be a hobby, that would be civil service and possibly a career.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>I see no difference in a character twinked by a high end character, and someone who bought plat to twink a character.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I do.  For starters a person twinked by a high level character gets some instructions passed on along the way.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And on that note how many of you have kicked someone from your group for being a super twink?...prolly none because that person is helping you at the time, and how do you know they didnt pay for that char w/ RL cash?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I have.  On more than one occasion. Why?  Because they had no clue how to play the character properly and they were <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> helping the group.  They were hindering it.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>And for all the people that are mad cause some people choose to bend the rules on a video game. I would REALLY love to follow you around for a day or 2 and point out every rule/law that you choose to ignore. My guess is that you would break far more than you would imagine<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I keep aware of the laws I break.  It doesn't mean I don't break laws.  But I have a reason when I do and I consider the impact on those around me.  <br>
<br>
See there are laws, but then there is also something called the social contract.  The social contract is not an official, codified system like law.  It's a collection of customs and beliefs designed to make daily life manageable for a society.  There is no law, for example, that enforces standing in line at the restaurant.  It's just that society fails to fuction correctly if people don't line up.  So people do it.  In theory, a restaurant owner can choose to eject people who ignore lines, and the police will enforce their right to eject people but how often does that happen?  Almost never.  Because the social contract is self-perpetuating and self-enforcing.<br>
<br>
So when people buy platinum I'm <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>far</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->less concerned that they've broken the rules than I am that they have violated the social contract.  Thus it doesn't matter what Sony does to discourage buying, what matters is what we, the members of the community, can do to bring about and maintain the environment we wish to spend our leisure time in.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>So instead of ranting and raving about someone doing something you dont agree with but causes no real damage to you or anyone around you,<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
One or two people buying some platinum doesn't really affect us.  One or two people making billions from exploits, flooding the market and devaluing the currency to the point where honest players can no longer play the game as it was intended for them to play, does. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=erivthedrow>ErivTheDrow</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/4/03 10:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4286.topic&index=132>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Buying Platinum</span><hr size=1> ok but you still havent shown me how someone can ruin your fun by buying or selling plat...is it because market prices arent where &quot;you&quot; think they should be or what?.../shrug<br>
